  "description": "A couplet is a pair of successive lines of verse, usually linked by [rhyme](./rhyme.md) and often forming a complete syntactic and thematic unit. The couplet is one of the smallest structural units in poetry — two lines — yet it can function as a self-contained poem, a [stanza](./stanza.md) form, or a closing gesture.",
